====Noun====
{{en-noun}}

# {{label|en|zoology}} An animal of the [[subkingdom]] [[Articulata]].

===Etymology 2===
From the adjective.

====Pronunciation====
* {{a|UK}} {{enPR|ärtĭ'kyəlāt}}, {{IPA|/ɑː(ɹ)ˈtɪk.jʊ.leɪt/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{enPR|ärtĭ'kyəlāt}}, {{IPA|/ɑːɹˈtɪk.jə.leɪt/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-articulate-verb.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}

====Verb====
{{en-verb|articulat}}

# To make clear or effective.
# To speak clearly; to [[enunciate]].
#: ''I wish he’d '''articulate''' his words more clearly.''
# To [[explain]]; to put into words; to make something [[specific]].
#: ''I like this painting, but I can’t '''articulate''' why.''
# To bend or hinge something at intervals, or to allow or build something so that it can bend.
#: ''an '''articulated''' bus''
# {{context|music|lang=en}} to [[attack]] a [[note]], as by [[tonguing]], [[slur]]ring, [[bow]]ing, etc.
#: '''''Articulate''' that passage heavily.''
# {{context|anatomy|lang=en}} to form a joint or connect by joints
#: ''The lower jaw '''articulates''' with the skull at the temporomandibular joint.''
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} To treat or make terms.
#: {{rfquotek|Shakespeare}}

